<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="switch-v">switch <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /swɪtʃ/    美 /swɪtʃ/  </p>
<p>vt &amp; vi</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>开 / 关 (电器等设备)</strong></h4>
<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>改变；转变</strong></h4>
<p>to change from one thing to another：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He <strong>switched</strong> the conversation <strong>from</strong> one subject <strong>to</strong> another. 
他把话题换来换去。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We’d take the train into the city center, then <strong>switch to</strong> the tram. 
我们乘火车到市中心，接着换乘电车。</p><footer>2012 湖北改</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>交换；调换</strong></h4>
<p>to exchange one thing for another：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You drive first and then we’ll switch round. 
你先开车，过一会儿咱们再换着开。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="switch-off">switch off</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>关上 (电灯、电视等)；[非正式用语] 不听；不理睬：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please switch off the TV when you go to bed.
睡觉时请关上电视。</p><footer>北师大① – 1</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Thankfully, I’ve learned to switch off and let it go over my head.
谢天谢地，我已经学会了不再烦恼，把它抛到脑后。</p></div>

<h3 id="switch-on">switch on</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>打开 (电灯、电视等)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I hear that song whenever I switch on the radio.
每次打开收音机时我们都能听到那首歌。</p><footer>外研④ – 3</footer></div>

<h3 id="switch-over">switch over</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>改变；转换：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We’ve switched over to telephone banking.
我们已经改用电话银行服务了。</p></div></div>